[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating AuthConfigFactory behavior**\n\nI’m considering that if the `AuthConfigFactory.factory` stays null after the test, future calls to `getFactory` will fail. It might be better to leave the factory set to the created `TestAuthConfigFactory` along with the class name property. That way, the future `getFactory` can return the factory without using reflection. However, if cleanup cannot restore, we shouldn't unset it. I think it’s wise to set the factory to null before the test to avoid any side effects.\n\n**Considering code placeholders**\n\nI’m thinking about whether I should leave a placeholder for the public or just delete it to reduce noise. Deleting the existing placeholder might be fine, especially since the commit is focused on tests. If all non-active tests are gone, I’ll need to check if there’s any source context, like module-info exports. I might also need to consider package accessibility and naming conventions too. This could really influence my decision!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_016b2fa145af3bdb0169f2fb78470481939dec47982ac04c26\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8vuITv68JLlYrUY8TNLV8bmT6a9p7m1GGQOE2wUT4IwZXyJI_Iqnd-ZDgNoyhl1qN70LTHV360Wiasp065dWYwPBJVv9N-0jbiAYAdt1VV7EjttcoDi_5xxZxNehnT9yAp-RkwpjGk639pFechJ6w_-vxehhlr1uyiRbHaWJFo307DY4GtmT_fs8unPgACS5pjiJJiujI6PrOXxqTCogMvZcaPCIn43KsehOQoujwWDraLxXn7i2TQW_yuECR_vdDWlf5hAoBI2QlClV9Nd7egMMpcQAHd0HEpl8YkD0ONmUWJ8L0Or6Ig986HZrE6lX7J7zrilUTPSpXAEGuu7K0CFinU0IlibnE5nWs-kXiIghEiqwRj5sON7dlFeMkDBIXny3A1WqN-jnDYEvJhorw4bah8rRB0ir7aMG9wa--HIf7Q9pg8WQl-tW6GmeTuSYCnMC0GhrsUncvmiwUyBD6lL73slspp9vPYS-YA4aH59GVGrb7ij4f36GEMFMfRcO2g4COUkymRb1epHJXAVEGQo8XnO_nMeF-c3Z4GUNJi9whgrAG9MPM4BhHznjW8ULZnYdtIMGlmRUUH_H5Q1s4qgpnVAD6KH3LoUKqd4wuBre0J-np3lpX4hxsXuFluz1APWt6LL1zt5w4I-zAdfembe5DiO7-jNcencxkvNwQkC_D6B0gI2r_dzbpxgKAO1z-Emp_XwkhjyBKi1WlGpWJ4utmd7QXjHsa6EQn_5nTEa2ihnBYajs